						<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en"><span dir="auto">List of United States counties and county-equivalents</span></h1>

<p>This is a complete list of the 3143 <a href="/wiki/County_(United_States)" title="County (United States)">counties</a> and <a href="/wiki/County-equivalent" title="County-equivalent">county-equivalents</a> of the <a href="/wiki/United_States" title="United States">United States of America</a> as of March 15, 2013<sup class="plainlinks noprint asof-tag update" style="display:none;"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=List_of_United_States_counties_and_county-equivalents&amp;action=edit">[update]</a></sup>. For more detailed information, see the individual state lists <a href="#See_also">shown below</a>.</p>
<p>In the United States, a county is a political and geographic subdivision of a <a href="/wiki/U.S._state" title="U.S. state">state</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-NACO_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-NACO-1"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> Of the 50 U.S. states, 48 states are divided into a total of 3007 counties.<sup id="cite_ref-PopEstCounties_2-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-PopEstCounties-2"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup> The number of counties per state ranges from the <a href="/wiki/List_of_counties_in_Delaware" title="List of counties in Delaware">three counties</a> of <a href="/wiki/Delaware" title="Delaware">Delaware</a> to the <a href="/wiki/List_of_counties_in_Texas" title="List of counties in Texas">254 counties</a> of <a href="/wiki/Texas" title="Texas">Texas</a>. The <a href="/wiki/List_of_counties_in_Rhode_Island" title="List of counties in Rhode Island">five counties</a> of <a href="/wiki/Rhode_Island" title="Rhode Island">Rhode Island</a>, the <a href="/wiki/List_of_counties_in_Connecticut" title="List of counties in Connecticut">eight counties</a> of <a href="/wiki/Connecticut" title="Connecticut">Connecticut</a>, and <a href="/wiki/List_of_counties_in_Massachusetts" title="List of counties in Massachusetts">eight of the 14 counties</a> of <a href="/wiki/Massachusetts" title="Massachusetts">Massachusetts</a> no longer have functional county governments, but continue to exist as legal and census entities.</p>
<p>Instead of counties, <a href="/wiki/Louisiana" title="Louisiana">Louisiana</a> is divided into <a href="/wiki/List_of_parishes_in_Louisiana" title="List of parishes in Louisiana">64 parishes</a> which are functionally identical to counties. <a href="/wiki/Alaska" title="Alaska">Alaska</a> is divided into <a href="/wiki/List_of_boroughs_and_census_areas_in_Alaska" title="List of boroughs and census areas in Alaska">18 organized boroughs</a> and a single <a href="/wiki/Unorganized_Borough,_Alaska" title="Unorganized Borough, Alaska">Unorganized Borough</a>. The <a href="/wiki/United_States_Census_Bureau" title="United States Census Bureau">United States Census Bureau</a> has divided the Unorganized Borough of Alaska into 11 census areas for federal census and planning purposes. In addition to their counties, the states of <a href="/wiki/Virginia" title="Virginia">Virginia</a>, <a href="/wiki/Maryland" title="Maryland">Maryland</a>, <a href="/wiki/Missouri" title="Missouri">Missouri</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Nevada" title="Nevada">Nevada</a> also have a total of <a href="/wiki/Independent_city_(United_States)" title="Independent city (United States)">42 independent cities</a> which are not a part of any county. The Census Bureau and the <a href="/wiki/Office_of_Management_and_Budget" title="Office of Management and Budget">Office of Management and Budget</a> consider the 64 parishes, 18 organized boroughs, 11 census areas, 42 independent cities, and the <a href="/wiki/Washington,_D.C." title="Washington, D.C.">District of Columbia</a> to be county-equivalents.</p>

<p><br /></p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Table">Table</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=List_of_United_States_counties_and_county-equivalents&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: Table">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>The following <a href="/wiki/Help:Sorting" title="Help:Sorting">sortable</a> <a href="/wiki/Help:Table" title="Help:Table">table</a> lists the 3143 <a href="/wiki/County_(United_States)" title="County (United States)">counties</a> and <a href="/wiki/County-equivalent" title="County-equivalent">county-equivalents</a> of the <a href="/wiki/United_States" title="United States">United States</a> with the following information:</p>
<ol>
<li>The <a href="/wiki/International_Committee_for_Information_Technology_Standards" title="International Committee for Information Technology Standards">International Committee for Information Technology Standards</a> (INCITS) county and county-equivalent code.<sup id="cite_ref-PopEstCounties_2-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-PopEstCounties-2"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup></li>
<li>The county or county-equivalent name.<sup id="cite_ref-PopEstCounties_2-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-PopEstCounties-2"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup></li>
<li>The <a href="/wiki/U.S._state" title="U.S. state">state</a> or <a href="/wiki/Washington,_D.C." title="Washington, D.C.">federal district</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-PopEstCounties_2-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-PopEstCounties-2"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup></li>
<li>The county and county-equivalent rank by population as of July 1, 2012, as estimated by <a href="/wiki/United_States_Census_Bureau" title="United States Census Bureau">United States Census Bureau</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-PopEstCounties_2-4" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-PopEstCounties-2"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup></li>
<li>The population of the county or county-equivalent as of July 1, 2012, as estimated by United States Census Bureau.<sup id="cite_ref-PopEstCounties_2-5" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-PopEstCounties-2"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup></li>
<li>The <a href="/wiki/Core_Based_Statistical_Area" title="Core Based Statistical Area">Core Based Statistical Area</a> if designated by the <a href="/wiki/Office_of_Management_and_Budget" title="Office of Management and Budget">Office of Management and Budget</a><sup id="cite_ref-OMB_13-01_3-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-OMB_13-01-3"><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup></li>
<li>The <a href="/wiki/Combined_Statistical_Area" title="Combined Statistical Area">Combined Statistical Area</a> if designated by the Office of Management and Budget.<sup id="cite_ref-OMB_13-01_3-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-OMB_13-01-3"><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup></li>
</ol>
<div style="clear:both;"></div>
<table class="wikitable sortable">
<caption><big>The 3143 counties and county-equivalents of the United&#160;States of America</big><br />
<br /></caption>
<tr>
<th><a href="/wiki/International_Committee_for_Information_Technology_Standards" title="International Committee for Information Technology Standards">INCITS</a></th>
<th><a href="/wiki/County_(United_States)" title="County (United States)">County</a> or <a href="/wiki/County-equivalent" title="County-equivalent">equivalent</a></th>
<th><a href="/wiki/U.S._state" title="U.S. state">State</a> or <a href="/wiki/Washington,_D.C." title="Washington, D.C.">district</a></th>
<th><a href="/wiki/United_States_Census_Bureau" title="United States Census Bureau">Rank</a></th>

<div class="reflist references-column-count references-column-count-2" style="-moz-column-count: 2; -webkit-column-count: 2; column-count: 2; list-style-type: decimal;">

<li id="cite_note-Borough-4"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Borough_4-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Borough_4-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Borough_4-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Borough_4-3"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Borough_4-4"><sup><i><b>e</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Borough_4-5"><sup><i><b>f</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Borough_4-6"><sup><i><b>g</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Borough_4-7"><sup><i><b>h</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Borough_4-8"><sup><i><b>i</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Borough_4-9"><sup><i><b>j</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Borough_4-10"><sup><i><b>k</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Borough_4-11"><sup><i><b>l</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Borough_4-12"><sup><i><b>m</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Borough_4-13"><sup><i><b>n</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text">This is one of the <a href="/wiki/List_of_boroughs_and_census_areas_in_Alaska" title="List of boroughs and census areas in Alaska">18 organized boroughs</a> of <a href="/wiki/Alaska" title="Alaska">Alaska</a>.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Census_Area-5"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Census_Area_5-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Census_Area_5-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Census_Area_5-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Census_Area_5-3"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Census_Area_5-4"><sup><i><b>e</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Census_Area_5-5"><sup><i><b>f</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Census_Area_5-6"><sup><i><b>g</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Census_Area_5-7"><sup><i><b>h</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Census_Area_5-8"><sup><i><b>i</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Census_Area_5-9"><sup><i><b>j</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Census_Area_5-10"><sup><i><b>k</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text">This is one of the <a href="/wiki/List_of_boroughs_and_census_areas_in_Alaska" title="List of boroughs and census areas in Alaska">11 census areas</a> of the <a href="/wiki/Unorganized_Borough,_Alaska" title="Unorganized Borough, Alaska">Unorganized Borough</a> of <a href="/wiki/Alaska" title="Alaska">Alaska</a>.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Anchorage-6"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Anchorage_6-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The <a href="/wiki/Anchorage,_Alaska" title="Anchorage, Alaska">Municipality of Anchorage, Alaska</a> has a fully <a href="/wiki/Consolidated_city%E2%80%93county" title="Consolidated city–county" class="mw-redirect">consolidated city and borough government</a>.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Juneau-7"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Juneau_7-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The <a href="/wiki/Juneau,_Alaska" title="Juneau, Alaska">City and Borough of Juneau, Alaska</a> has a fully <a href="/wiki/Consolidated_city%E2%80%93county" title="Consolidated city–county" class="mw-redirect">consolidated city and borough government</a>.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Sitka-8"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Sitka_8-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The <a href="/wiki/Sitka,_Alaska" title="Sitka, Alaska">City and Borough of Sitka, Alaska</a> has a fully <a href="/wiki/Consolidated_city%E2%80%93county" title="Consolidated city–county" class="mw-redirect">consolidated city and borough government</a>.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Yakutat-9"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Yakutat_9-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The <a href="/wiki/Yakutat,_Alaska" title="Yakutat, Alaska">City and Borough of Yakutat, Alaska</a> has a fully <a href="/wiki/Consolidated_city%E2%80%93county" title="Consolidated city–county" class="mw-redirect">consolidated city and borough government</a>.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-San_Francisco-10"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-San_Francisco_10-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The <a href="/wiki/San_Francisco" title="San Francisco">City and County of San Francisco, California</a> has a fully <a href="/wiki/Consolidated_city%E2%80%93county" title="Consolidated city–county" class="mw-redirect">consolidated city and county government</a>.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Broomfield-11"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Broomfield_11-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The <a href="/wiki/Broomfield,_Colorado" title="Broomfield, Colorado">City and County of Broomfield, Colorado</a> has a fully <a href="/wiki/Consolidated_city%E2%80%93county" title="Consolidated city–county" class="mw-redirect">consolidated city and county government</a>.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Denver-12"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Denver_12-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The <a href="/wiki/Denver" title="Denver">City and County of Denver, Colorado</a> has a fully <a href="/wiki/Consolidated_city%E2%80%93county" title="Consolidated city–county" class="mw-redirect">consolidated city and county government</a>.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Nogov-13"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Nogov_13-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Nogov_13-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Nogov_13-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Nogov_13-3"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Nogov_13-4"><sup><i><b>e</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Nogov_13-5"><sup><i><b>f</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Nogov_13-6"><sup><i><b>g</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Nogov_13-7"><sup><i><b>h</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Nogov_13-8"><sup><i><b>i</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Nogov_13-9"><sup><i><b>j</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Nogov_13-10"><sup><i><b>k</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Nogov_13-11"><sup><i><b>l</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Nogov_13-12"><sup><i><b>m</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Nogov_13-13"><sup><i><b>n</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Nogov_13-14"><sup><i><b>o</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Nogov_13-15"><sup><i><b>p</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Nogov_13-16"><sup><i><b>q</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Nogov_13-17"><sup><i><b>r</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Nogov_13-18"><sup><i><b>s</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Nogov_13-19"><sup><i><b>t</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Nogov_13-20"><sup><i><b>u</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text">This county has no functional county government.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-DC-14"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-DC_14-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The <a href="/wiki/United_States_Census_Bureau" title="United States Census Bureau">United States Census Bureau</a> and the <a href="/wiki/Office_of_Management_and_Budget" title="Office of Management and Budget">Office of Management and Budget</a> consider the <a href="/wiki/Washington,_D.C." title="Washington, D.C.">District of Columbia</a> to be a <a href="/wiki/County-equivalent" title="County-equivalent">county-equivalent</a>.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Honolulu-15"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Honolulu_15-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The <a href="/wiki/Honolulu_County,_Hawaii" title="Honolulu County, Hawaii">City and County of Honolulu, Hawaii</a> has a <a href="/wiki/Consolidated_city%E2%80%93county" title="Consolidated city–county" class="mw-redirect">county government with municipal functions</a>.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Baltimore-16"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Baltimore_16-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The <a href="/wiki/Baltimore" title="Baltimore">City of Baltimore, Maryland</a> is an <a href="/wiki/Independent_city_(United_States)" title="Independent city (United States)">independent city</a> exclusive of any county.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Nantucket-17"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Nantucket_17-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The <a href="/wiki/Nantucket,_Massachusetts" title="Nantucket, Massachusetts" class="mw-redirect">Town and County of Nantucket, Massachusetts</a> has a fully <a href="/wiki/Consolidated_city%E2%80%93county" title="Consolidated city–county" class="mw-redirect">consolidated town and county government</a>.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-St._Louis-18"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-St._Louis_18-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The <a href="/wiki/St._Louis" title="St. Louis">City of St. Louis, Missouri</a> is an <a href="/wiki/Independent_city_(United_States)" title="Independent city (United States)">independent city</a> exclusive of any county.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Carson_City-19"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Carson_City_19-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The <a href="/wiki/Carson_City,_Nevada" title="Carson City, Nevada">Consolidated Municipality of Carson City, Nevada</a> is an <a href="/wiki/Independent_city_(United_States)" title="Independent city (United States)">independent city</a> exclusive of any county.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Los_Alamos-20"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Los_Alamos_20-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="/wiki/Los_Alamos_County,_New_Mexico" title="Los Alamos County, New Mexico">Los Alamos County, New Mexico</a> has a <a href="/wiki/Consolidated_city%E2%80%93county" title="Consolidated city–county" class="mw-redirect">county government with municipal functions</a>.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-VAIC-21"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-VAIC_21-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-VAIC_21-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a <p>This is a complete list of the 3143 <a href="/wiki/County_(United_States)" title="County (United States)">counties</a> and <a href="/wiki/County-equivalent" title="County-equivalent">county-equivalents</a> of the <a href="/wiki/United_States" title="United States">United States of America</a> as of March 15, 2013<sup class="plainlinks noprint asof-tag update" style="display:none;"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=List_of_United_States_counties_and_county-equivalents&amp;action=edit">[update]</a></sup>. For more detailed information, see the individual state lists <a href="#See_also">shown below</a>.</p>
<p>In the United States, a county is a political and geographic subdivision of a <a href="/wiki/U.S._state" title="U.S. state">state</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-NACO_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-NACO-1"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> Of the 50 U.S. states, 48 states are divided into a total of 3007 counties.<sup id="cite_ref-PopEstCounties_2-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-PopEstCounties-2"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup> The number of counties per state ranges from the <a href="/wiki/List_of_counties_in_Delaware" title="List of counties in Delaware">three counties</a> of <a href="/wiki/Delaware" title="Delaware">Delaware</a> to the <a href="/wiki/List_of_counties_in_Texas" title="List of counties in Texas">254 counties</a> of <a href="/wiki/Texas" title="Texas">Texas</a>. The <a href="/wiki/List_of_counties_in_Rhode_Island" title="List of counties in Rhode Island">five counties</a> of <a href="/wiki/Rhode_Island" title="Rhode Island">Rhode Island</a>, the <a href="/wiki/List_of_counties_in_Connecticut" title="List of counties in Connecticut">eight counties</a> of <a href="/wiki/Connecticut" title="Connecticut">Connecticut</a>, and <a href="/wiki/List_of_counties_in_Massachusetts" title="List of counties in Massachusetts">eight of the 14 counties</a> of <a href="/wiki/Massachusetts" title="Massachusetts">Massachusetts</a> no longer have functional county governments, but continue to exist as legal and census entities.</p>
<p>Instead of counties, <a href="/wiki/Louisiana" title="Louisiana">Louisiana</a> is divided into <a href="/wiki/List_of_parishes_in_Louisiana" title="List of parishes in Louisiana">64 parishes</a> which are functionally identical to counties. <a href="/wiki/Alaska" title="Alaska">Alaska</a> is divided into <a href="/wiki/List_of_boroughs_and_census_areas_in_Alaska" title="List of boroughs and census areas in Alaska">18 organized boroughs</a> and a single <a href="/wiki/Unorganized_Borough,_Alaska" title="Unorganized Borough, Alaska">Unorganized Borough</a>. The <a href="/wiki/United_States_Census_Bureau" title="United States Census Bureau">United States Census Bureau</a> has divided the Unorganized Borough of Alaska into 11 census areas for federal census and planning purposes. In addition to their counties, the states of <a href="/wiki/Virginia" title="Virginia">Virginia</a>, <a href="/wiki/Maryland" title="Maryland">Maryland</a>, <a href="/wiki/Missouri" title="Missouri">Missouri</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Nevada" title="Nevada">Nevada</a> also have a total of <a href="/wiki/Independent_city_(United_States)" title="Independent city (United States)">42 independent cities</a> which are not a part of any county. The Census Bureau and the <a href="/wiki/Office_of_Management_and_Budget" title="Office of Management and Budget">Office of Management and Budget</a> consider the 64 parishes, 18 organized boroughs, 11 census areas, 42 independent cities, and the <a href="/wiki/Washington,_D.C." title="Washington, D.C.">District of Columbia</a> to be county-equivalents.</p>

<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Table">Table</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=List_of_United_States_counties_and_county-equivalents&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: Table">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>The following <a href="/wiki/Help:Sorting" title="Help:Sorting">sortable</a> <a href="/wiki/Help:Table" title="Help:Table">table</a> lists the 3143 <a href="/wiki/County_(United_States)" title="County (United States)">counties</a> and <a href="/wiki/County-equivalent" title="County-equivalent">county-equivalents</a> of the <a href="/wiki/United_States" title="United States">United States</a> with the following information:</p>
<ol>
<li>The <a href="/wiki/International_Committee_for_Information_Technology_Standards" title="International Committee for Information Technology Standards">International Committee for Information Technology Standards</a> (INCITS) county and county-equivalent code.<sup id="cite_ref-PopEstCounties_2-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-PopEstCounties-2"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup></li>
<li>The county or county-equivalent name.<sup id="cite_ref-PopEstCounties_2-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-PopEstCounties-2"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup></li>
<li>The <a href="/wiki/U.S._state" title="U.S. state">state</a> or <a href="/wiki/Washington,_D.C." title="Washington, D.C.">federal district</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-PopEstCounties_2-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-PopEstCounties-2"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup></li>
<li>The county and county-equivalent rank by population as of July 1, 2012, as estimated by <a href="/wiki/United_States_Census_Bureau" title="United States Census Bureau">United States Census Bureau</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-PopEstCounties_2-4" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-PopEstCounties-2"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup></li>
<li>The population of the county or county-equivalent as of July 1, 2012, as estimated by United States Census Bureau.<sup id="cite_ref-PopEstCounties_2-5" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-PopEstCounties-2"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup></li>
<li>The <a href="/wiki/Core_Based_Statistical_Area" title="Core Based Statistical Area">Core Based Statistical Area</a> if designated by the <a href="/wiki/Office_of_Management_and_Budget" title="Office of Management and Budget">Office of Management and Budget</a><sup id="cite_ref-OMB_13-01_3-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-OMB_13-01-3"><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup></li>
<li>The <a href="/wiki/Combined_Statistical_Area" title="Combined Statistical Area">Combined Statistical Area</a> if designated by the Office of Management and Budget.<sup id="cite_ref-OMB_13-01_3-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-OMB_13-01-3"><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup></li>
</ol>

<ul>

</ul>

<ul>
